# 3. Custom Entity API  

_**author: Cool_Loong, Superice666**_  
The custom entity API is in the package `cn.nukkit.entity.custom`.  
To create a new custom entity, you need to implement `CustomEntity` interface.

## Minimum Feasible Example  
There must be a constructor like `Entity(FullChunk chunk, CompoundTag nbt)` in your CustomEntity class, 
here is a simple example:   

```java
public class MyPig extends Entity implements CustomEntity {
    public final static CustomEntityDefinition def = CustomEntityDefinition.builder().identifier("powernukkitx:boar")
            .summonable(true)
            .spawnEgg(false)
            .build();
    public MyPig(FullChunk chunk, CompoundTag nbt) {
        super(chunk, nbt);
    }
    public int getNetworkId() {
        return getDefinition().getRuntimeId();
    }
    public CustomEntityDefinition getDefinition() {
        return def;
    }
    public String getOriginalName() {//自定义实体显示名
        return "boar";
    }
}
```

## Register Custom Entities
You can invoke `Entity#registerCustomEntity(CustomEntityProvider customEntityProvider)` to register your custom entities.

`CustomClassEntityProvider` is a simple implementation of CustomEntityProvider, which allows you to register a custom
entity by only its class instance. There are 2 ways to create it :  
1.`CustomClassEntityProvider(Class<? extends Entity> customEntityClass)`
A custom entity class is required to be passed in, and there is a `CustomEntityDefinition` static final field named `def` in the class

2.`CustomClassEntityProvider(CustomEntityDefinition customEntityDefinition, Class<? extends Entity> customEntityClass)`  
Requires passing in a custom entity class and the `CustomEntityDefinition` of the custom entity.

## Custom Human with AI
This custom entity borrows the behavior group of zombies in the PNX AI framework, 
and its behavior is consistent with that of zombies, which can attack players.
For more information about entity AI, see the [tutorial](https://doc.powernukkitx.cn/en-us/dev/java/entity-ai/behavior.html)  

```java
public class MyHuman extends EntityIntelligentHuman implements CustomEntity {
    public final static CustomEntityDefinition def = CustomEntityDefinition.builder().identifier("powernukkitx:human")
            .summonable(false)
            .spawnEgg(false)
            .build(); // Entity def
    public MyHuman(FullChunk chunk, CompoundTag nbt) {
        super(chunk, nbt);
        Skin skin = new Skin(); // Create a new skin for this entiy
        skin.setTrusted(true);// Set the skin as trusted
        skin.setSkinId("Standard_Custom");
        skin.setSkinData(Base64.getDecoder().decode(""));
        this.setSkin(skin);
        this.getInventory().addItem(Item.get(ItemID.DIAMOND_SWORD));
    }
    public IBehaviorGroup requireBehaviorGroup() { // AI behaviors
        return new BehaviorGroup(
                this.tickSpread,
                Set.of(),
                Set.of(
                        new Behavior(new MeleeAttackExecutor(CoreMemoryTypes.ATTACK_TARGET, 0.3f, 40, true, 10), all(
                                new MemoryCheckNotEmptyEvaluator(CoreMemoryTypes.ATTACK_TARGET),
                                entity -> !entity.getMemoryStorage().notEmpty(CoreMemoryTypes.ATTACK_TARGET) || !(entity.getMemoryStorage().get(CoreMemoryTypes.ATTACK_TARGET) instanceof Player player) || player.isSurvival()
                        ), 3, 1),
                        new Behavior(new MeleeAttackExecutor(CoreMemoryTypes.NEAREST_PLAYER, 0.3f, 40, false, 10), all(
                                new MemoryCheckNotEmptyEvaluator(CoreMemoryTypes.NEAREST_PLAYER),
                                entity -> {
                                    if (entity.getMemoryStorage().isEmpty(CoreMemoryTypes.NEAREST_PLAYER))
                                        return true;
                                    Player player = entity.getMemoryStorage().get(CoreMemoryTypes.NEAREST_PLAYER);
                                    return player.isSurvival();
                                }
                        ), 2, 1),
                        new Behavior(new FlatRandomRoamExecutor(0.3f, 12, 100, false, -1, true, 10), (entity -> true), 1, 1)
                ),
                Set.of(new NearestPlayerSensor(40, 0, 20)),
                Set.of(new WalkController(), new LookController(true, true)),
                new SimpleFlatAStarRouteFinder(new WalkingPosEvaluator(), this),
                this
        );
    }
    public CustomEntityDefinition getDefinition() {
        return def;
    }
}
```
